==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Turnus
<hw>Tur"nus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>Turnus</ets>, the king of the Rutuli, mentioned in the
Aeneid.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A common, large, handsome,
American swallowtail butterfly, now regarded as one of the forms of
<spn>Papilio glaucus</spn> syn. <spn>Jasoniades glaucus</spn>. The wings
are yellow, margined and barred with black, and with an orange-red spot
near the posterior angle of the hind wings. Called also <altname>tiger
swallowtail</altname>. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under
<er>Swallowtail</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turnverein</ent>⟦br⟧
